{"id": "EUVD-2025-32805", "enisaUuid": "6f614913-2d9b-32e5-b69c-e4633c9651d4", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: mcp-2221: prevent UAF in delayed work\n\nIf the device is plugged/unplugged without giving time for mcp_init_work()\nto complete, we might kick in the devm free code path and thus have\nunavailable struct mcp_2221 while in delayed work.\n\nCanceling the delayed_work item is enough to solve the issue, because\ncancel_delayed_work_sync will prevent the work item to requeue itself.", "datePublished": "2025-10-01T11:42:30", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T11:42:30", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53459", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/47e91fdfa511139f2549687edb0d8649b123227b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5dc297652dbc557eba7ca7d6a4c5f1940dffffb1"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53459", "GHSA-prrg-pvxw-q4m2"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3cc28b68-f34e-3e0f-b1f9-f22514107713", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.2"}, {"id": "6c71d80f-91e2-3b41-8d9c-139fc4a9ec3c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3"}, {"id": "89933106-4dfb-3ec3-8046-c76bdb5103c9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "cacb1e85-948e-38b3-8dc7-7b08b44d060b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "960f9df7c620ecb6030aff1d9a6c3d67598b8290 <47e91fdfa511139f2549687edb0d8649b123227b"}, {"id": "cef46f89-be34-32e1-9ca1-67c604b67f0a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "960f9df7c620ecb6030aff1d9a6c3d67598b8290 <5dc297652dbc557eba7ca7d6a4c5f1940dffffb1"}, {"id": "e34c6d62-05fd-3096-a2c4-16864e9e50b5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "95a371c6-fdde-34b2-8195-406a5a98e94d", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}